 {"id":"bd-10x","title":"Implement Style struct with cascading/merging","description":"# Implement Style struct with cascading/merging

## Background & Strategic Importance
Style is the unified styling type that combines colors, attributes, and modifiers into a single composable unit. It has a high bottleneck score (95.6) because 14+ downstream tasks depend on it. Every widget, text span, and theme uses Style.

**Design Philosophy:**
- Option-wrapped fields enable CSS-like inheritance where unset properties inherit from parent
- Explicit masks clarify what is "set" vs "unset" (per Plan Section 0.6)
- Zero-cost when no style applied

---

## Technical Design

### Core Structure

```rust
use tracing::{trace, instrument};

/// Unified styling type with CSS-like cascading semantics.
///
/// # Design Rationale
/// - Option fields allow inheritance (None = inherit from parent)
/// - Explicit masks track which properties are intentionally set
/// - Copy + small size (24 bytes) for cheap passing
/// - Builder pattern for ergonomic construction
#[derive(Clone, Copy, Debug, Default, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub struct Style {
    /// Foreground color (text color)
    pub fg: Option<PackedRgba>,
    /// Background color
    pub bg: Option<PackedRgba>,
    /// Text attributes (bold, italic, etc.)
    pub attrs: Option<StyleFlags>,
    /// Underline color (separate from fg for flexibility)
    pub underline_color: Option<PackedRgba>,
}

/// Text attribute flags.
#[derive(Clone, Copy, Debug, Default, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub struct StyleFlags(u16);

impl StyleFlags {
    pub const NONE: Self = Self(0);
    pub const BOLD: Self = Self(1 << 0);
    pub const DIM: Self = Self(1 << 1);
    pub const ITALIC: Self = Self(1 << 2);
    pub const UNDERLINE: Self = Self(1 << 3);
    pub const BLINK: Self = Self(1 << 4);
    pub const REVERSE: Self = Self(1 << 5);
    pub const HIDDEN: Self = Self(1 << 6);
    pub const STRIKETHROUGH: Self = Self(1 << 7);
    pub const DOUBLE_UNDERLINE: Self = Self(1 << 8);
    pub const CURLY_UNDERLINE: Self = Self(1 << 9);

    pub fn contains(&self, other: Self) -> bool {
        (self.0 & other.0) == other.0
    }

    pub fn insert(&mut self, other: Self) {
        self.0 |= other.0;
    }

    pub fn remove(&mut self, other: Self) {
        self.0 &= !other.0;
    }
}
```

### Builder Pattern

```rust
impl Style {
    /// Create an empty style (all properties inherit).
    pub const fn new() -> Self {
        Self {
            fg: None,
            bg: None,
            attrs: None,
            underline_color: None,
        }
    }

    /// Set foreground color.
    pub const fn fg(mut self, color: PackedRgba) -> Self {
        self.fg = Some(color);
        self
    }

    /// Set background color.
    pub const fn bg(mut self, color: PackedRgba) -> Self {
        self.bg = Some(color);
        self
    }

    /// Add bold attribute.
    pub fn bold(mut self) -> Self {
        self.add_attr(StyleFlags::BOLD)
    }

    /// Add italic attribute.
    pub fn italic(mut self) -> Self {
        self.add_attr(StyleFlags::ITALIC)
    }

    /// Add underline attribute.
    pub fn underline(mut self) -> Self {
        self.add_attr(StyleFlags::UNDERLINE)
    }

    /// Add dim attribute.
    pub fn dim(mut self) -> Self {
        self.add_attr(StyleFlags::DIM)
    }

    /// Add reverse video attribute.
    pub fn reverse(mut self) -> Self {
        self.add_attr(StyleFlags::REVERSE)
    }

    /// Add strikethrough attribute.
    pub fn strikethrough(mut self) -> Self {
        self.add_attr(StyleFlags::STRIKETHROUGH)
    }

    /// Add an attribute flag.
    fn add_attr(mut self, flag: StyleFlags) -> Self {
        match &mut self.attrs {
            Some(attrs) => attrs.insert(flag),
            None => self.attrs = Some(flag),
        }
        self
    }

    /// Set underline color.
    pub fn underline_color(mut self, color: PackedRgba) -> Self {
        self.underline_color = Some(color);
        self
    }
}
```

### Cascading/Merging

```rust
impl Style {
    /// Cascade merge: Fill in None fields from parent.
    ///
    /// `child.merge(parent)` returns a style where child's Some values
    /// take precedence, and parent fills in any None values.
    ///
    /// # Example
    /// ```
    /// let parent = Style::new().fg(RED).bold();
    /// let child = Style::new().bg(BLUE);
    /// let merged = child.merge(&parent);
    /// // merged has: fg=RED (from parent), bg=BLUE (from child), bold (from parent)
    /// ```
    #[instrument(skip(self, parent))]
    pub fn merge(&self, parent: &Style) -> Style {
        trace!("Merging child into parent");
        Style {
            fg: self.fg.or(parent.fg),
            bg: self.bg.or(parent.bg),
            attrs: match (self.attrs, parent.attrs) {
                (Some(c), Some(p)) => Some(StyleFlags(c.0 | p.0)),
                (Some(c), None) => Some(c),
                (None, Some(p)) => Some(p),
                (None, None) => None,
            },
            underline_color: self.underline_color.or(parent.underline_color),
        }
    }

    /// Patch merge: Override parent with child's Some values.
    ///
    /// `parent.patch(&child)` returns a style where child's Some values
    /// replace parent's values.
    ///
    /// This is the inverse perspective of merge().
    pub fn patch(&self, child: &Style) -> Style {
        child.merge(self)
    }

    /// Check if this style has any properties set.
    pub fn is_empty(&self) -> bool {
        self.fg.is_none()
            && self.bg.is_none()
            && self.attrs.is_none()
            && self.underline_color.is_none()
    }

    /// Check if a specific attribute is set.
    pub fn has_attr(&self, flag: StyleFlags) -> bool {
        self.attrs.map_or(false, |a| a.contains(flag))
    }
}
```

### Conversion to CellStyle

```rust
/// Convert Style to CellStyle for rendering.
///
/// CellStyle is the compact format stored in cells, while Style
/// is the ergonomic format used in API.
impl From<Style> for CellStyle {
    fn from(style: Style) -> Self {
        CellStyle {
            fg: style.fg.unwrap_or(PackedRgba::WHITE),
            bg: style.bg.unwrap_or(PackedRgba::TRANSPARENT),
            attrs: style.attrs.map(|a| CellAttrs::from_flags(a))
                .unwrap_or(CellAttrs::NONE),
        }
    }
}
```

