## Frame Features Used

- `frame.cursor_position` - Set where the cursor should appear
- `frame.cursor_visible` - Control cursor visibility

## Migration Pattern

1. Change signature to use Frame
2. Set cursor position for text inputs:
   ```rust
   fn render(&self, area: Rect, frame: &mut Frame) {
       let buf = &mut frame.buffer;

       // ... draw the input widget ...

       // Position cursor at current input position
       if self.focused {
           let cursor_x = area.x + self.cursor_offset as u16;
           let cursor_y = area.y;
           frame.cursor_position = Some((cursor_x, cursor_y));
           frame.cursor_visible = true;
       }
   }
   ```

## Widgets Expected in This Category

Based on functionality (to be confirmed by audit):
- TextInput
- MultilineInput (if exists)
- SearchBox (if exists)
